Rajeev Sharma wrote:
&gt; Hi All,
&gt; 
&gt; I am trying to setup heritrix crawler for my projject. I am not able
&gt; to run my first job in heritrix. I get an error saying &quot;failed to
&gt; crawl job&quot;.
&gt; 
&gt; Failed to crawl seed 	http://www.archive.org/
&gt; 
&gt; Please help me setup my crawler. below is my configuration file

You should start with one of the bundled default configurations, then 
change it minimally to create your job.

For the heart of the crawler, the set of &#39;Processors&#39; run against each 
URI in series, your crawl is set up to run a &#39;Preselector&#39; 5 times in a 
row. As this is an optional Processor type which only rechecks scope, 
and does none of the actual fetching/extracting/writing/updating 
necessary for a crawl to proceed, this won&#39;t work.

I suggest you start fresh with a default, do a tiny crawl with only the 
absolutely necessary changes (your user-agent and operator-from-address 
identifiers) to verify everything else is alright, then try more 
advanced customization.

Also, I recommend using the latest released version (1.12.1) rather than 
an older version (1.10.0).

- Gordon @ IA


